hh3cPortal.name: hh3cPortal
hh3cPortal.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cPortal.description: The MIB module is used for managing portal.

hh3cPortalMaxUserNumber.name: hh3cPortalMaxUserNumber
hh3cPortalMaxUserNumber.description: Specify the maximum number of online users, the value to be set should meet the following two conditions: 1. Less than or equal to hh3cPortalUserNumberUpperLimit. 2. Greater than or equal to one. The default value is equal to hh3cPortalUserNumberUpperLimit.

hh3cPortalCurrentUserNumber.name: hh3cPortalCurrentUserNumber
hh3cPortalCurrentUserNumber.description: The current number of users connecting to the portal.

hh3cPortalStatus.name: hh3cPortalStatus
hh3cPortalStatus.description: It indicates the portal status. enabled: Portal is enabled on one or more interfaces. disabled: Portal is not enabled on any interface.

hh3cPortalNasId.name: hh3cPortalNasId
hh3cPortalNasId.description: The nas id of this device.

hh3cPortalServerTable.name: hh3cPortalServerTable
hh3cPortalServerTable.description: This table defines the name and URL of portal server. It can not be created and destroyed by MIB.

hh3cPortalServerEntry.name: hh3cPortalServerEntry
hh3cPortalServerEntry.description: There is a row in this table for each name and URL of portal server. It is indexed using the object hh3cPortalServerName.

hh3cPortalServerName.name: hh3cPortalServerName
hh3cPortalServerName.description: It is the index of the table of hh3cPortalServerTable, it shows the name of the portal server.

hh3cPortalServerUrl.name: hh3cPortalServerUrl
hh3cPortalServerUrl.description: It shows the uniform resource locator to the portal server. Users which have not logon to portal will be redirected to the portal server according to hh3cPortalServerUrl. The value is consisted of protocol, IP address and relative path. For example: HTTP://10.1.1.1/portal It is not configurable when the portal server has been enabled.

hh3cPortalServerPort.name: hh3cPortalServerPort
hh3cPortalServerPort.description: It shows the UDP port of the portal server. The port will be used when client sends packets to portal server. Default value is 50100. It is not configurable when the portal server has been enabled.

hh3cPortalIfInfoTable.name: hh3cPortalIfInfoTable
hh3cPortalIfInfoTable.description: This table describes the portal information on some interface.

hh3cPortalIfInfoEntry.name: hh3cPortalIfInfoEntry
hh3cPortalIfInfoEntry.description: There is a row in this table for a interface on which portal has been enabled. It is indexed using the object ifIndex.

hh3cPortalAuthReqNumber.name: hh3cPortalAuthReqNumber
hh3cPortalAuthReqNumber.description: It shows the number of authentication request messages which are sent by portal module to AAA module.

hh3cPortalAuthSuccNumber.name: hh3cPortalAuthSuccNumber
hh3cPortalAuthSuccNumber.description: It shows the number of authentication success response messages which are sent by AAA module to portal module.

hh3cPortalAuthFailNumber.name: hh3cPortalAuthFailNumber
hh3cPortalAuthFailNumber.description: It shows the number of authentication failure response messages which are sent by AAA module to portal module.

hh3cPortalIfServerTable.name: hh3cPortalIfServerTable
hh3cPortalIfServerTable.description: This table describes the portal information on some interface.

hh3cPortalIfServerEntry.name: hh3cPortalIfServerEntry
hh3cPortalIfServerEntry.description: There is a row in this table for a interface on which portal has been enabled. It is indexed using the object ifIndex.

hh3cPortalIfServerIndex.name: hh3cPortalIfServerIndex
hh3cPortalIfServerIndex.description: It is the index of the table of hh3cIfPtServerTable, it shows the index of the portal server.

hh3cPortalIfServerUrl.name: hh3cPortalIfServerUrl
hh3cPortalIfServerUrl.description: It shows the uniform resource locator to the portal server. Users which have not logon to portal will be redirected to the portal server according to hh3cPortalServerIfUrl. The value is consisted of protocol, IP address and relative path. For example: HTTP://10.1.1.1/portal It is not configurable when the portal server has been enabled.

hh3cPortalIfServerRowStatus.name: hh3cPortalIfServerRowStatus
hh3cPortalIfServerRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which support active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, portal server must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the portal server MUST NOT be referred by interface.

hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDTable.name: hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDTable
hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDTable.description: This table describes the interface on which portal has been enabled, the Vlan that the interface belongs to and the NAS ID to which the Vlan is bound.

hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDEntry.name: hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDEntry
hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDEntry.description: There is a row in this table for a interface on which portal has been enabled, the Vlan that the interface belongs to and the NAS ID to which the Vlan is bound. It is indexed using the object ifIndex and Vlan that the interface belongs to.

hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDIfIndex.name: hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDIfIndex
hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDIfIndex.description: It is the index of the table of hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDTable, it shows the interface on which portal has been enabled.

hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDVlanID.name: hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDVlanID
hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDVlanID.description: It is the index of the table of hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDTable, it shows the Vlan that the interface belongs to.

hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDNasID.name: hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDNasID
hh3cPortalIfVlanNasIDNasID.description: It is the NAS ID to which the Vlan is bound to.

hh3cPortalSSIDFreeRuleSrcSSID.name: hh3cPortalSSIDFreeRuleSrcSSID

hh3cPortalMacTriggerSrvIPAddrType.name: hh3cPortalMacTriggerSrvIPAddrType
hh3cPortalMacTriggerSrvIPAddrType.description: The type of MAC Trigger Portal server IP address. While other types of addresses are defined in the InetAddressType textual convention, and DNS names, a classifier can only look at packets on the wire.

hh3cPortalMacTriggerSrvRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which support active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation.

hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfIfIndex.name: hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfIfIndex
hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfIfIndex.description: It is the interface index and the index of hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfTable.

hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfDetctFlowPeriod.name: hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfDetctFlowPeriod
hh3cPortalMacTriggerOnIfDetctFlowPeriod.description: It shows the period of detecting the user flow when MAC Trigger and Portal is enabled. The unit is second.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcMac.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcMac
hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcMac.description: The MAC address to match against the packet's source MAC address.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleAddrType.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleAddrType
hh3cPortalFreeRuleAddrType.description: The type of IP address used by this classifier entry. While other types of addresses are defined in the InetAddressType textual convention, and DNS names, a classifier can only look at packets on the wire.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcAddr.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcAddr
hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcAddr.description: The IP address to match against the packet's source IP address. This may be a DNS name or an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix. hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcPrefix indicates the number of bits that are relevant.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcPrefix.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcPrefix
hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcPrefix.description: The length of the CIDR Prefix carried in hh3cPortalFreeRuleSrcAddr. In IPv4 addresses, a length of 0 indicates a match of any address; a length of 32 indicates a match of a single host address, and a length between 0 and 32 indicates the use of a CIDR Prefix. IPv6 is similar, except that prefix lengths range from 0..128.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstAddr.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstAddr
hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstAddr.description: The IP address to match against the packet's destination IP address. This may be a DNS name or an IPv4 or IPv6 prefix. hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPrefix indicates the number of bits that are relevant.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPrefix.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPrefix

IPv6 is similar, except that prefix lengths range from 0..128.

hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPort.name: hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPort
hh3cPortalFreeRuleDstPort.description: The destination port allows users to access.

hh3cPortalServerLost.name: hh3cPortalServerLost
hh3cPortalServerLost.description: This trap is generated when the device finds that the portal server is unreachable, the portal server's name is hh3cPortalServerName, and the portal server's IP is hh3cPortalServerIP, and the portal server's port is hh3cPortalServerPort, and the portal server has been enabled.

hh3cPortalServerGet.name: hh3cPortalServerGet
hh3cPortalServerGet.description: This trap is generated when the device finds that the state of portal server changes from unreachable state to reachable, the portal server's name is hh3cPortalServerName, and the portal server's IP is hh3cPortalServerIP, and the portal server's port is hh3cPortalServerPort, and the portal server has been enabled.

hh3cPortalStatAuthReq.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthReq
hh3cPortalStatAuthReq.description: It shows the total number of portal authentication requests from the portal server.

hh3cPortalStatAckLogout.name: hh3cPortalStatAckLogout
hh3cPortalStatAckLogout.description: It shows the number of logout requests from the portal server.

hh3cPortalStatNotifyLogout.name: hh3cPortalStatNotifyLogout
hh3cPortalStatNotifyLogout.description: It shows the number of logout requests from the access device.

hh3cPortalStatChallengeTimeout.name: hh3cPortalStatChallengeTimeout
hh3cPortalStatChallengeTimeout.description: It shows the number of challenge from the portal server without response.

hh3cPortalStatChallengeBusy.name: hh3cPortalStatChallengeBusy
hh3cPortalStatChallengeBusy.description: It shows the number of device-busy responses for challenges from the portal server.

hh3cPortalStatChallengeFail.name: hh3cPortalStatChallengeFail
hh3cPortalStatChallengeFail.description: It shows the number of challenges from the portal server with failure response.

hh3cPortalStatAuthTimeout.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthTimeout
hh3cPortalStatAuthTimeout.description: It shows the number of authentication requests from the portal server without responses.

hh3cPortalStatAuthFail.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthFail
hh3cPortalStatAuthFail.description: It shows the number of authentication requests from the portal server with failure responses.

hh3cPortalStatPwdError.name: hh3cPortalStatPwdError
hh3cPortalStatPwdError.description: It shows the number of password errors.

hh3cPortalStatAuthBusy.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthBusy
hh3cPortalStatAuthBusy.description: It shows the number of device-busy responses to authentication requests from the portal server.

hh3cPortalStatAuthDisordered.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthDisordered
hh3cPortalStatAuthDisordered.description: It shows the number of disordered authentication packets from the portal server.

hh3cPortalStatAuthUnknownError.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthUnknownError
hh3cPortalStatAuthUnknownError.description: It shows the number of unknown errors.

hh3cPortalStatAuthResp.name: hh3cPortalStatAuthResp
hh3cPortalStatAuthResp.description: It shows the number of authentication response messages which are sent by device to portal server.

hh3cPortalStatChallengeReq.name: hh3cPortalStatChallengeReq
hh3cPortalStatChallengeReq.description: It shows the number of challenge request messages which are sent by portal server to device.

hh3cPortalStatChallengeResp.name: hh3cPortalStatChallengeResp
hh3cPortalStatChallengeResp.description: It shows the number of challenge response messages which are sent by device to portal server.

hh3cPortalStatHttpResp.name: hh3cPortalStatHttpResp
hh3cPortalStatHttpResp.description: It shows the number of http response messages which are sent by device to portal user.

hh3cPortalPktStaReqAuthNum.name: hh3cPortalPktStaReqAuthNum
hh3cPortalPktStaReqAuthNum.description: It shows the total number of portal authentication requests from the portal server.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthSuccess.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthSuccess
hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthSuccess.description: It shows the total number of the response to REQ-AUTH packet of portal server including error code 0 in the packet, that is authentication success.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthReject.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthReject
hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthReject.description: It shows the total number of the response to REQ-AUTH packet of portal server including error code 1 in the packet, that is rejected by server.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthEstablish.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthEstablish
hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthEstablish.description: It shows the total number of the response to REQ-AUTH packet of portal server including error code 2 in the packet, that is the link is already established.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthBusy.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthBusy
hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthBusy.description: It shows the total number of the response to REQ-AUTH packet of portal server including error code 3 in the packet, that is the system is busy.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthAuthFail.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthAuthFail
hh3cPortalPktStaAckAuthAuthFail.description: It shows the total number of the response to REQ-AUTH packet of portal server including error code 4 in the packet, that is authentication fail.

hh3cPortalPktStaReqChallengeNum.name: hh3cPortalPktStaReqChallengeNum
hh3cPortalPktStaReqChallengeNum.description: It shows the total number of portal challenge requests from the portal server.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeSuccess.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeSuccess
hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeSuccess.description: It shows the total number of the response to challenge packet of portal server including error code 0 in the packet, that is challenge is success.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeReject.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeReject
hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeReject.description: It shows the total number of the response to challenge packet of portal server including error code 1 in the packet, that is challenge is rejected by server.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeEstablish.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeEstablish
hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeEstablish.description: It shows the total number of the response to challenge packet of portal server including error code 2 in the packet, that is the link is alreadys established.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeBusy.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeBusy
hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeBusy.description: It shows the total number of the response to challenge packet of portal server including error code 3 in the packet, that is the system is busy.

hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeAuthFail.name: hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeAuthFail
hh3cPortalPktStaAckChallengeAuthFail.description: It shows the total number of the response to challenge packet of portal server including error code 4 in the packet, that is authentication fail.
